  "local_port": 35220,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Universal?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at Universal can be an exciting experience. Here are some key things new employees should know to help them prepare for their first day:\n\n### 1. **Dress Code**\n   - **Attire:** Depending on your role, you might need to adhere to specific dress codes. For example, if you're working in a themed area, costumes may be required. Otherwise, business casual attire is typically expected.\n   - **Comfort:** Wear comfortable shoes, especially if your role involves a lot of walking or standing.\n\n### 2. **Arrival and Parking**\n   - **Arrival Time:** Plan to arrive early to account for traffic and parking. Being punctual is crucial.\n   - **Parking:** Familiarize yourself with employee parking areas. There may be designated lots or specific parking passes required.\n\n### 3. **Orientation and Training**\n   - **Orientation:** You\u2019ll likely start with an orientation session that covers company policies, safety procedures, and an overview of your role.\n   - **Training:** Depending on your position, you might have on-the-job training or classroom-style sessions.\n\n### 4. **Company Culture**\n   - **Teamwork:** Universal emphasizes teamwork and guest satisfaction. Be prepared to collaborate with colleagues.\n   - **Guest Experience:** A significant focus is placed on ensuring guests have a magical experience. Understanding and prioritizing this will be key.\n\n### 5. **Security and Safety**\n   - **Badges:** You\u2019ll receive an employee badge for identification. Keep it visible at all times while on property.\n   - **Safety Protocols:** Pay close attention to safety protocols, especially if you\u2019re working in areas with rides or attractions.\n\n### 6. **Benefits and Resources**\n   - **Employee Benefits:** You\u2019ll receive information about health benefits, time off, and other perks. Make sure to ask any questions during orientation.\n   - **Employee Discounts:** Universal often offers discounts on park admissions, merchandise, and dining for employees.\n\n### 7. **Communication Tools**\n   - **Email and Intranet:** You\u2019ll likely be given access to an internal email system and an intranet with company resources and updates.\n   - **Walkie-Talkies or Radios:** Depending on your role, you might use communication devices to stay in touch with your team.\n\n### 8. **Lunch and Breaks**\n   - **Break Areas:** There are designated areas for employees to take breaks. These might be different from guest areas.\n   - **Meal Options:** There may be employee cafeterias or discounts at park dining locations.\n\n### 9. **Getting Around**\n   - **Park Layout:** Familiarize yourself with the park layout to navigate efficiently. You might receive a map or guide during orientation.\n   - **Transportation:** If applicable, understand the employee transportation options available, like shuttles.\n\n### 10. **Asking Questions**\n   - **Be Proactive:** Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions. Your supervisors and colleagues are there to help you succeed.\n\n### Additional Tips\n- **Bring a Notebook:** Taking notes during orientation and training can be very helpful.\n- **Stay Hydrated:** Especially in warm weather, staying hydrated is important.\n- **Be Enthusiastic:** A positive attitude can go a long way in making a great first impression.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, you\u2019ll be better prepared for your first day at Universal and set yourself up for a successful start to your new job.",
